<subSubSection id="C35F655A85409967CC04E652FD37F9B0" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="1" pageNumber="224" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFA36D185409964CC04E652FF6EF982" blockId="1.[106,227,1587,1611]" box="[106,227,1587,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385409964CC04E652FF6EF982" bold="true" box="[106,227,1587,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">Etymology:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36D185409967CC04E638FD37F9B0" blockId="1.[106,1097,1625,1650]" lastBlockId="2.[189,1180,1449,1657]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">
<materialsCitation id="3B2D3C8C85409967CC04E638FD3BF9B0" country="Iran" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="225" location="Zagros Mountains" pageId="1" pageNumber="224" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Tehran">
The specific epithet is the classical name for what is known today as the ruins of Rayy in 
<collectingCountry id="F352764185409964C879E63BFBC8F9B8" box="[1047,1093,1626,1649]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="224">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Rayy lies inside of the greater metropolitan area of 
<collectingRegion id="4981F83385439967CEA0E5C8FC9BFA08" box="[718,790,1449,1473]" country="Iran" name="Tehran" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Tehran</collectingRegion>
and was built by the Median Empire approximately 5000 years ago. The Greeks called the area comprising modern 
<collectingRegion id="4981F83385439967CF9EE5A9FBD5FA29" box="[1008,1112,1480,1504]" country="Iran" name="Kordestan" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Kurdistan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4981F83385439967C80BE5A9FF73FA36" country="Iran" name="Azarbayjan-e Sharqi" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Azerbaijan</collectingRegion>
, and northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F352764185439967CDA0E586FE75FA37" box="[462,504,1511,1534]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Iran</collectingCountry>
(roughly 
<collectingRegion id="4981F83385439967CE0AE586FD35FA36" box="[612,696,1511,1535]" country="Iran" name="Esfahan" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Esfahan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4981F83385439967CEA8E586FCA2FA36" box="[710,815,1511,1535]" country="Iran" name="Hamadan" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Hamedan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4981F83385439967CF55E586FC0BFA36" box="[827,902,1511,1535]" country="Iran" name="Tehran" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Tehran</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4981F83385439967CFFAE586FC6DFA36" box="[916,992,1511,1535]" country="Iran" name="Zanjan" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Zanjan</collectingRegion>
, and neighboring provinces around the 
<location id="8E9A600A85439967CDF5E667FDD1F9D4" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EC87C785409966CCDBE1CEFDBBFD31:8E9A600A85439967CDF5E667FDD1F9D4" box="[411,604,1541,1566]" country="Iran" name="Zagros Mountains" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" stateProvince="Tehran">Zagros Mountains</location>
, although the ancient Median Empire at times extended further south in modern 
<collectingCountry id="F352764185439967CDD2E644FE6BF9F5" box="[444,486,1573,1596]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Iran</collectingCountry>
and as far east as Kashmir) “Medea” or “Media” [the Latin adjective of which is 
<emphasis id="B931EAC385439967CD5EE622FEF7F992" box="[304,378,1603,1627]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">median</emphasis>
(“in the middle”), and for which 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285439967CEA2E622FC3FF992" authority="ENGEL" authorityName="ENGEL" box="[716,946,1603,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediana">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385439967CEA2E622FCE4F992" box="[716,873,1603,1627]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Osmia mediana</emphasis>
ENGEL
</taxonomicName>
from nearby Karaj was named], and the people of the region, the Medes
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF3A665985439967CCA8E501FE42FA5A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4779369" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4779369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4779369/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" startId="2.[198,236,1376,1398]" targetBox="[198,1173,174,1369]" targetPageId="2">
