<subSubSection id="C35F655A85429966CC04E0CEFDBBFD31" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFA36D185429966CC04E0CEFF68FF0E" blockId="3.[106,229,175,199]" box="[106,229,175,199]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CC04E0CEFF68FF0E" bold="true" box="[106,229,175,199]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Comments:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36D185429966CC04E0B4FE05FE0D" blockId="3.[106,1096,213,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
The new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CDBBE0B7FD12FF24" authority="ENGEL" authorityName="ENGEL" box="[469,671,213,237]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Chiasmognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pashupati">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CDBBE0B7FE6BFF24" box="[469,486,214,237]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CD9AE0B4FDDEFF24" box="[500,595,213,237]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">pashupati</emphasis>
ENGEL
</taxonomicName>
from southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F352764185429966CF07E0B4FC4FFF24" box="[873,962,213,237]" name="Pakistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
. Both have a similar castaneous coloration overall, although somewhat more light in 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CF55E095FC17FEC5" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2008" box="[827,922,244,268]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Chiasmognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhagae">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CF55E095FCC1FEC2" box="[827,844,244,267]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CF37E095FC17FEC5" box="[857,922,244,268]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">rhagae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CFC8E095FF26FEE2" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Chiasmognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhagae">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CFC8E095FF26FEE2" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Chiasmognathus rhagae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has the clypeus and supraclypeal area noticeably yellow in comparison to the otherwise castaneous head (
<figureCitation id="137E2A5485429966CD4AE150FEECFE80" box="[292,353,305,329]" captionStart="Figs 1-3" captionStartId="2.[198,236,1376,1398]" captionTargetBox="[198,1173,174,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-108@2.[198,1173,174,1369]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-3: Photomicrographs of holotype female of Chiasmognathus rhagae nov. sp. (1) lateral aspect; (2) dorsal aspect; (3) facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4779369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4779369/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). More significantly, however, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CE83E153FCE6FE80" box="[749,875,305,329]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Chiasmognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pashupati">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CE83E153FD73FE80" box="[749,766,306,329]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CF62E150FCE6FE80" box="[780,875,305,329]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">pashupati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other described species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CCBFE131FEFEFEA1" box="[209,371,336,360]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Chiasmognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CCBFE131FEFEFEA1" box="[209,371,336,360]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Chiasmognathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have some degree of mesoscutal punctation and sculpturing, 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CF87E131FBC5FEA1" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2008" box="[1001,1096,336,360]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Chiasmognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhagae">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CF87E131FC77FEAE" box="[1001,1018,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966C869E131FBC5FEA1" box="[1031,1096,336,360]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">rhagae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a smooth, polished, and impunctate mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="137E2A5485429966CEC2E10EFD67FE4E" box="[684,746,367,391]" captionStart="Figs 1-3" captionStartId="2.[198,236,1376,1398]" captionTargetBox="[198,1173,174,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-108@2.[198,1173,174,1369]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-3: Photomicrographs of holotype female of Chiasmognathus rhagae nov. sp. (1) lateral aspect; (2) dorsal aspect; (3) facial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4779369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4779369/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). In this last feature, 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CFBEE10EFBBDFE4E" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2008" box="[976,1072,367,391]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Chiasmognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhagae">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CFBEE10EFC6CFE4F" box="[976,993,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CF81E10EFBBDFE4E" box="[1007,1072,367,391]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">rhagae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to an undescribed species from 
<collectingCountry id="F352764185429966CD95E1EFFDCDFE6C" box="[507,576,398,421]" name="Yemen" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Yemen</collectingCountry>
but differs in the fact that the latter is dark brown to black among other traits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36D185429966CCDBE26AFD0CFDEA" blockId="3.[181,641,523,548]" box="[181,641,523,548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CCDBE26AFD0CFDEA" authority="(WARNCKE)" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" box="[181,641,523,548]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Chiasmognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="aeg" subSpecies="yptiacus">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CCDBE26AFD0CFDEA" bold="true" box="[181,641,523,548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CCDBE26AFE77FDED" bold="true" box="[181,506,523,548]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Chiasmognathus aeg yptiacus</emphasis>
(WARNCKE)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36D185429966CC04E226FC72FDB4" blockId="3.[106,1096,583,637]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B931EAC385429966CC04E226FF60FD96" bold="true" box="[106,237,583,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">New record:</emphasis>
3 , 
<collectingCountry id="F352764185429966CD2DE226FE10FD96" box="[323,413,583,607]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">ISRAEL</collectingCountry>
: Negev, Sapir gas station, 15.v.98 [
<date id="FFFB101185429966CF7BE226FC23FD96" box="[789,942,583,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="1998-05-15">15 May 1998</date>
], L. Packer, at 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D5285429966CC04E204FF78FDB4" box="[106,245,613,637]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Nomioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
